    "narrative": "The Austin Waves are primed for a high-ceiling performance today, anchored by **Gunnar Henderson**, who earns our premier efficiency score of 81.88. **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from an aggressive combination of a +16% park factor and an ideal leadoff spot against the middling arm of Brayan Bello. While his 34% rain risk warrants a close eye on the weather, his current projection stands as the clear cornerstone of our offense. **Kyle Tucker** (73.75) and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (66.25) provide the secondary high-leverage scoring, with both capitalizing on favorable xERA matchups and strong peripheral metrics like xwOBA. We are specifically looking for **Heliot Ramos** (58.46) to exploit the slow delivery of Sandy Alcantara; his efficiency score is boosted by a wind-out scenario and the heightened potential for a stolen base, a category where our organization remains hyper-focused on maintaining an advantage.\n\nOur most difficult decision occurred at the bench, where **Coby Mayo** (53.88) narrowly missed the cut. Despite **Coby Mayo** benefiting from the same positive park environment as **Gunnar Henderson**, his projected spot at the bottom of the order and a negative platoon split against right-handed pitching ultimately forced the optimizer to favor **Andy Pages** (60.68) and **Dominic Smith** (53.74). We are remaining cautious with **Luis Robert Jr.** (50.66), whose upside is currently stifled by a difficult dynamic platoon disadvantage; should his lineup positioning shift or weather reports worsen for our primary assets, we are prepared to pivot to the high-floor versatility of **Nolan Schanuel** or **Josh Lowe** from the bench to preserve our seasonal game caps.",
